  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b90\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bcb\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Man arrested with ice drug",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Kalmunai Special Task Force has arrested a suspect who smuggled 20 grams of ice drug on a motorcycle.",
        "The arrest took place in an operation carried out by the Kalmunai Special Task Force in Amparai District on Sunday night of the 03rd Batticaloa Banana Paper Mill Military Intelligence Unit.",
        "The arrested suspect is a 30-year-old from Kalmunai area and was ready to smuggle the drug to Otamawadi area of \u200b\u200bBatticaloa when he was arrested at a ground near Kalmunai beach school in Amparai district.",
        "It is worth noting that the special task force seized a motorcycle containing 20 grams of ice drug packed with two mobile phones from the arrested suspect.",
        "The operation was conducted under the guidance of Special Task Force Commanding Officer Deputy Inspector General of Police Varuna Jayasundhara, Ampara Zonal Officer Siresta Police Superintendent JR Senathira, District Assistant Superintendent of Police DC Vevidavithana, Kalmunai Special Task Force Camp Officer-in-Charge Police Inspector R.A.T.C.S. Police Sergeants Bandara (13443), Weerakoon (33354), Police Constables Nimes (90699), Rajapaksa (24812), Driver WM Gunapala (19401) and the Investigation Unit, headed by Rathnayake, conducted the operation. They proceeded and arrested the suspect.",
        "During this, after making a call to purchase drugs from the said suspect, Banana Paper Investigation Officers made a call.",
        "The suspect was summoned to a certain place and arrested by Kalmunai Special Task Force who went in disguise at that place.",
        "It is noted that later the arrested person was taken to the Kalmunai police along with the evidence by the Special Task Force for court proceedings."
      ],
